\app~has been running in one of Alibaba's large e-commerce system for more then five months, and we manually check whether all the root cause of alarms of this week were located every week. Among them, 5 of the 6 online alarm cases from May 8 to May 12 were hit, with a hit rate of 83\%; the three alarm cases from May 15 to May 21 were all hit, with a hit rate of 100\%;
In addition, compared with the method of manually checking and analyzing the root cause of the alarm, \app~can find the root cause in about 3 minutes, while the traditional manual inspection of the root cause of the alarm usually takes more then 30 minutes.

Usually, in order to find more detail information about the root cause node, we will use drill-down logic in practice.
That is to go deep into the node at the end of the anomaly propagation chain to see what anomalies inside it, such as JVM Full GC, high TCP retransmission rate, etc..
The detail information of these faults helps to understand the real root cause of the anomaly calls between services, and a quick recovery strategy can be formulated based on this information.

But in the practice of enterprises, we also encountered some problems:
\emph{1)} business metrics cause alarm,but the system metrics are normal....
\emph{2)} the abnormal time series metrics exceeds the detection time window, resulting in failure to locate the root cause....
\emph{3)} algorithm model has false negatives and false positives...
\emph{4)} the system metrics of some services is not covered....
